---
description: Python FastAPI backend rules for API and testing
globs:
  - "app/**/*.py"
  - "tests/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

General rules:
- Prefer simple, readable, maintainable code.
- Do not add unnecessary abstractions or libraries.
- Do not hardcode secrets, credentials, URLs, or tokens.
- Use type hints where reasonable.
- Use environment variables for configuration.
- When changing behavior, update or add tests.
- Add comments to document functions, classes and important code. 
- Document code in README.md

FastAPI rules:
- Keep route handlers thin.
- Put business logic in service module.
- Use clear HTTP status codes.
- Raise HTTPException for API errors.
- Add /health for process health.
- Add /ready for app and dependency readiness.

Testing rules:
- Use pytest.
- Add tests for every new endpoint.
- Test both successful and failing cases.
- Do not rely on production environment variables in tests.

Logging and errors:
- Use structured, meaningful logs.
- Do not swallow exceptions silently.
- Do not log secrets or sensitive values.
- Return user-friendly API errors but keep internal details in logs.